Cette modification permet à la route "home" de matcher l'URL racine "/" même si des query params sont présents (comme "/?param1=value1&param2=value2"). L'astérisque * agit comme un wildcard qui capture tous les caractères qui suivent le /.


Add a regexp to match query params

I'll help you modify the home route pattern to properly match query parameters using a regular expression.

<patch>
<title>Update home route to match query params</title>
<edit>
<path>app/src/app/routes/common.jsx</path>
<description>Update the route pattern to match any query parameters after the root path using a regular expression</description>
<operation>update</operation>
<old_text>router.use('home', '/?', function () {</old_text>
<new_text>router.use('home', /^\/?(?:\?.*)?$/, function () {</new_text>
</edit>
</patch>

This change replaces the simple path pattern with a regular expression that:
- `^` matches start of string
- `\/?` optionally matches a forward slash
- `(?:\?.*)?` optionally matches a question mark followed by any characters (query parameters)
- `$` matches end of string

This will match URLs like:
- `/`
- `/?param=value`
- `/?param1=value1&param2=value2`
